<br>
An Amazon Messenger, a brown haired, green eyed woman.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yasoo, Athelfi&quot;, Sarabi said smiling. The Messenger smiled and returned the greeting, she handed a scroll to Sarabi and gave her farewells. She left leaving Sar there with a letter.<br>
<br>
Sarabi shut the door and sat down on the sofa. She stared at the scroll for a moment. She touched the Egyptian symbol lightly with the tip of her finger. Sarabi grinned, perhaps a Welcome letter and a safe journeys wish..The Priestess opened it and read it..<br>
<br>
**-Dear Sarabi of Athens,<br>
<br>
I send this letter with sorrow in my heart. I regret to inform you that our great Queen, Cleopatra: Daughter of the Nile, has passed on to her next life. We mourn this great loss yet celebrate that she is to return to us in her next life. You will still be paid, but only half sum. We thank you for offering your services to our Queen but our new Ruler wishes that the Stargate be built by an Egyptian. Thank you, Egypt welcomes you anytime and considers you an ally. May the Gods smile on you.<br>
<br>
-Shepseskare, Royal Scribe of Egypt**<br>
<br>
Sarabi sighed. Cleopatra was a great Queen, and a even better friend. She roughly placed the letter on the in-tale beside the sofa and went off to her room to unpack. Hastily, she pushed her clothes back into her closet, and went to the very back room of her and Kayce's yurt, it was closed off from the rest of the hut. Sar pushed open the door to her Laboratory and unpacked her materials. The High Priestess of Athena left her shoulder bag there and went outside. She walked over to the stables and unloaded a few things from Teo's saddle bag. When she made it back to her and Kayce's hut, Sarabi placed everything back in its proper position. With a huff, the Favored of Athena sat down on her sofa.<br>
<br>
The death of Cleopatra had upset her, who could kill someone so honourable and caring? <p>-¤-Sarabi Aquila Falco-¤-<BR>
§High Priestess of Athena§<BR>
~Athena's Chosen~<BR>
